gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 140, Jazz 137
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns escape with a win and defeated the Jazz, 140-137, in 2OT. Kevin Durant recorded a game high 39 points, along with a season-high 10 assists, and eight rebounds for the Suns, with Devin Booker adding 26 points and eight assists in the victory. Lauri Markkanen tallied a season-high 38 points and 17 rebounds for the Jazz in the losing effort. The Suns improve to 7-6 in the regular season, while the Jazz fall to 4-9.
